title: U.S. strikes Iranian facility in Syria amid attacks on American troops
description: The Pentagon announcement coincided with a separate disclosure that a U.S. MQ-9 Reaper drone had been shot down off the coast of Yemen.

title: For Gaza’s journalists, war coverage and personal grief are one story
description: Journalists have been killed at a rate of at least one a day during the war.

title: Slovakia’s new government rejects aid for Ukraine
description: Slovak Prime Minister Robert Fico made good on a campaign promise to halt military assistance to Ukraine as his government rejected a $43 million package of rockets and ammunition.

title: Attacked by Amazon forest’s largest poisonous snake, a man fights to survive
description: Considered the largest poisonous snake in the Americas — and the world’s longest viper — the South American bushmaster injects up to 500 milligrams of venom into its victims.

title: Israeli troops fight in the heart of Gaza City amid global calls for pause
description: Israel’s defense minister said troops were fighting in the heart of Gaza City and dismissed the growing international calls for a cease-fire or humanitarian pause.

title: What’s the difference between a humanitarian pause and a cease-fire?
description: The terms, hotly debated during the Israel-Hamas war, may seem similar — but they have significant differences in scope and meaning, officials and experts say.

title: Rebel militias rout Sudanese army in Darfur, mass killings reported
description: The seven month old conflict has taken a new turn as the army appears to have been routed in much of Darfur, leaving the Rapid Support Forces in command.

title: U.S. top diplomat lays out fullest vision yet for Gaza’s future
description: The outline of a post-conflict vision by Secretary of State Antony Blinken came amid increasing concerns about Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s commitment to a Gaza administered by Palestinians.

title: As war frustrations rise, stalemate tests Zelensky and top general Zaluzhny
description: After 20 months of all-out war, public fissures are appearing in Ukraine’s previously unshakable national unity prompting the president to call for an end to ‘infighting.’

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Rashida Tlaib censured over remarks; Israel says forces in ‘heart of Gaza City’
description: The censure came after Rep. Tlaib (D-Mich.) posted a video accusing President Biden of supporting the “genocide” of Palestinians and urging him to back a cease-fire.

title: If Netanyahu has a long-term plan for Gaza, he isn’t sharing it
description: A month after one of the most shocking attacks on civilians in Israel’s history, Israel’s leader isn’t offering a clear plan for what comes after the war.
